import React, { useState } from "react"; import { Container, Button, Box, Typography, Table, TableBody, TableCell, TableContainer, TableHead, TableRow, Paper } from "@mui/material"; const App = () => { const [activeScreen, setActiveScreen] = useState('viewSubject'); // Track active screen const [academicData, setAcademicData] = useState([ { semester: 'Semester 1', math: 'A', science: 'B', history: 'C', english: 'A', art: 'E', geography: 'B', physics: 'A' }, { semester: 'Semester 2', math: 'B', science: 'A', history: 'B', english: 'C', art: 'D', geography: 'A', physics: 'B' }, ]); const [subjectsData, setSubjectsData] = useState([ { id: 1, subject: 'Math', staffName: 'Mr. John' }, { id: 2, subject: 'Science', staffName: 'Mrs. Smith' }, { id: 3, subject: 'History', staffName: 'Mr. Brown' }, { id: 4, subject: 'English', staffName: 'Ms. Lee' }, ]); const handleViewSubjectClick = () => setActiveScreen('viewSubject'); const handleAcademicPerformanceClick = () => setActiveScreen('academicPerformance'); return ( {activeScreen === 'viewSubject' && ( View Subject S.No Subject Staff Name {subjectsData.map((row, index) => ( {index + 1} {row.subject} {row.staffName} ))}
)} {activeScreen === 'academicPerformance' && ( Academic Performance Semester Math Science History English Art Geography Physics {academicData.map((row, index) => ( {row.semester} {row.math} {row.science} {row.history} {row.english} {row.art} {row.geography} {row.physics} ))}
)} ); }; export default App;
